        </ul>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Now, funded up and growing fast, Unit21\xe2\x80\x99s job is to build out the platform, one vertical at a time, balancing flexibility and simplicity, power and ease. When it pulls it off, it will have written the playbook for building broadly-applicable tools that feel custom-built.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         To understand what Unit21 is building, why it\xe2\x80\x99s important, and how you might be able to wield AI/ML even if you can\xe2\x80\x99t write a single line of code, we\xe2\x80\x99ll cover:
        </p>
        <ul style="margin: 1em 0;">
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            Founder-Market Fit
           </strong>
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            Meet Unit21
           </strong>
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            One Platform, Many Use Cases
           </strong>
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            Initial Market: Fighting Financial Fraud
           </strong>
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            Growth and Tiger and Growth, Oh My!
           </strong>
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            When I Needed Unit21
           </strong>
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            Blue Check and Beyond
           </strong>
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            Trade-Offs and Challenges
           </strong>
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            AI/ML to the People
           </strong>
          </p>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Unit21 exists because of a problem that both Trisha and Clarence faced: ops people aren\xe2\x80\x99t empowered to write their own business logic to fight suspicious activity. The results range from wasteful to disastrous.
        </p>
        <h3 style="-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: 'SF Compact Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;">
         <strong>
          Founder-Market Fit
         </strong>
        </h3>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Product-Market Fit is a well-known phenomenon in Startupland. Like porn, you know it when you see it, and Superhuman CEO Rahul Vohra helped popularize a
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkcuOwyAMRb-m7BLxzGPBYjbzGxEEJ0FNIALTKn8_tFmMZNlXtqxrHc8GYY3p0mfMSD5pwusEHeCdd0CEREqGNHmnWccHoeRInJaODWogPk9LAjiM3zWmAuQsdvezQR_Dd4NSrsimzdJZLkAICozPMLphhCo7BWq0ziy3rynOQ5hBwwvSFQOQXW-IZ36Inwf_rZHg5eHdLj5lTLEE187xqP0tvptcTkhbOUxobPE7NlVAWH2ABmOz-OCaM0VXZmwOk56AtYfEa045oz0dGFdKiZa1jHWW9cJSKXtnKLe0n6WwkjHZWWPlQ9Jj5W0uNqOZn58TSNIhoo3Jh7WOn5s5YP8OKpCp1qMEj9cEwdgd3M0Kb-RfetMKAVJ9hZsMfkCrXg5jJ8RAbzYVphgU68eRkersYt0K_6Z_jjuavw" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          method for measuring it
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Less well-known but equally important is Founder-Market Fit, the idea that certain people are just right to start certain types of companies.
        </p>
        <div class="captioned-image-container-static" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 16px; text-align: center;">
         <figure style="display: inline-block; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;">
          <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="image-wrapper" style="margin: 8px auto; mso-padding-alt: 1em 0 1.6em;" width="100%">
           <tbody>
            <tr>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
             </td>
             <td align="left" class="content" style="text-align: center;" width="550">
              <a class="image-link" href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxVUsuu3CAM_ZrJLhHvwCKLq0r9jciAk0E3gRTIvZ1-fZlkUVVCfso-xscOKq4pv6Yjldq9xVxfB04Rv8uGtWLuzoJ5Dn6iimkuhen8JDzVUnehzEtG3CFsU80ndsdpt-CghhSvCkKY7J4T9WZUjC6GwULFIg2VWgupnGMKcMEbF04fMDqc8AvzK0XstulZ61Ee_OPBfrbnfBzKaUsF9zm4tLdQ2GHFphes7vnWrU1ND_bj123wjzUl3_xlm4-c1oylhC9s8VIRj1ZxQzD5BpFvmCbs6T6x5XOPRFrrtOgtAO8FH7E3kuoevOXM4jgaLYbCB9jhT4rwXe65Wo97F5d5DVkukwDXki1LrxSaXhine8vA9GA9A8WtscbMVBHy2xAyHHHtwsQIo2QkmjIpJR_oQKmydOSWCDF6IMyS0QluBaVCWbDiIci-sv9W1eUppmpTDnFt6c8n7LhdiTbn3PR-xlBfM0awG_qbznpfxUXwvGLE3K7Fz1DftyBHoY3iXJObvsZ3-xodjaFdQ_apVcV_oH8BawnHVQ" style="border: none; display: block; height: auto; margin: 0; padding: 0; text-decoration: none; width: auto;" target="_blank">
               <img alt="" class="wide-image" data-attrs='{"src":"https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/0a3852ff-66e9-49c8-b2a9-abd2a63b9b99_1600x900.png","height":819,"width":1456,"resizeWidth":null,"bytes":null,"alt":null,"title":null,"type":null,"href":null}' src="https://cdn.substack.com/image/fetch/w_2912,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0a3852ff-66e9-49c8-b2a9-abd2a63b9b99_1600x900.png" style="-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; border: none !important; display: block; height: auto; margin: 0 auto; margin-bottom: 0; max-width: 550px; vertical-align: middle; width: 100%;" width="550"/>
              </a>
             </td>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
             </td>
            </tr>
           </tbody>
          </table>
         </figure>
        </div>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         This too was defined by a certain \xe2\x80\x9cJe ne sais quoi\xe2\x80\x9d until
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkM2OhCAQhJ9muI3hHzxw2Mu-hgFpHTIKBnBd335xPGzS6U6nUqnUN9oKc8qn2VKp6FpDPTcwEY6yQK2Q0V4gD8EbIqlmgvfIG-6JFhqFMkwZYLVhMTXvgLbdLWG0NaT4cWBMBXoZJR3vBVcSNJPccqop7oUaySQnKTS_c-3uA8QRDPxAPlMEtJhXrVt5sK8H_W5zHEcXp99uTGv7LlM7_FnCHMtzSnv0kJ-rzW-ozylcIgqGYkqwwppQIQTrSEeIdEQxhzlX3mLqsBo5c5wQLp11_MHxOtOu7K5UO76vNJRNTNWlHOLc5PfLrrB8hNZ4aHfdY6jnANG6BfwNo95MP3iGGSLkxtoPtl4kheK6l4xpfJdvtJgWRPU9QS3Zp-aK_6F_7yOL5A" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          NFX laid out four dimensions
         </a>
         that contribute to Founder-Market Fit:
        </p>
        <ol style="margin: 1em 0;">
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            Obsession
           </strong>
           : the founders can\xe2\x80\x99t stop thinking about the idea, work on it in their free time.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            Founder Story
           </strong>
           : customers need to see a compelling \xe2\x80\x9cwhy\xe2\x80\x9d in the founders\xe2\x80\x99 past.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            Personality
           </strong>
           : the founders need to fit in with peers in their target market.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            Experience
           </strong>
           : founders need to have just enough experience in the space, but not so much that they\xe2\x80\x99re set in their ways and not open to new approaches.
          </p>
         </li>
        </ol>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Trisha and Clarence hit all four for Unit21. They have tight Founder-Market Fit.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Trisha is an experienced engineering and product leader at one of the past half-decade\xe2\x80\x99s most successful startups, Affirm. Max Levchin, who founded both Affirm and PayPal, called her one of the best engineers in the country.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         She first experienced the issue because Affirm has to decide whether to let any given user \xe2\x80\x9cBuy Now, Pay Later\xe2\x80\x9d in near real-time. Essentially, Affirm underwrites loans at the point of sale. Fraud is a massive risk to the company. As
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkUmOwyAQRU8TdrEYPSxY9KavYTGUYxQb3FBuy7dvnERqCYH0S5-HHs4gPFI-9ZYKkmsb8dxARzjKAoiQyV4gj8Fr1vJeKDkQr6VnvepJKOOUAVYTFo15B7LtdgnOYEjx1aCUKzJr1TEBfBiYk1Ry3g7UgegBYPKcem7eXLP7ANGBhl_IZ4pAFj0jbuUmvm78u67jOJrtXCOWxqW1BmbHGSJ-kDXglA1XPk0hr_fg7_WqMH3m9ylXxn3LFRBfAYKbY_jZodQSCZpTzmhHe8aVUqJhDWOtZZ2wVMrOG8ot7ZwUVjImW2usvEm6PnhTdlvQuOf1LJJ1TGhTDvFRx8_ZrLC8BtXOWM91jwHPEaKxC_i3OHz7f6kcHxAh13_xo8HLuupkP7RC9PQtqpoVvWJdFUoq2afaiv_QP6KanYk" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          PYMNTS highlights
         </a>
         , \xe2\x80\x9cBotching authentication methods could lead Affirm to charge either a phantom or the wrong person, having its money vanish into the ether.\xe2\x80\x9d So the company employs a huge team of in-house engineers and data scientists to fight fraud. They\xe2\x80\x99re highly-paid talent playing table stakes defense instead of differentiated offense in a highly competitive space.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Clarence\xe2\x80\x99s experience is even more personal. Like Trisha, Clarence is a genius. He grew up in Singapore and came to the US on a government scholarship awarded to the top 50 students in the country each year. He used it to study computer science and AI at Stanford, then joined Shape Security as an engineer out of school (Shape was recently acquired by F5 for $1 billion). While at Shape, Clarence got bored and started submitting papers to security conferences on the side, for fun. They were good, and conferences flew him around the world to present them. His lectures caught the attention of tech publishing powerhouse O\xe2\x80\x99Reilly Media, who asked him to write a book. He did. It\xe2\x80\x99s called
         <em>
          <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkUuOwyAMhk9Tdo14BliwmM1cIzLBTVEJVIQ0yu2HtouRLD9l_dbnGRoupZ7uWbZG3m5q5xNdxmNL2BpWsm9YpxgcG7kRSloSnAzMKEPiNt0q4goxuVZ3JM_dpzhDiyV_NijlitwdpV7bGbS8GYmCghLUgwoaFBcYbvqrC3uImGd0-MJ6lowkuXtrz-0ifi78t9txHEOpGFM6h7msvZOir1DPnr0iHj2sMN9jxmtCqDnm5Qo59LbVhknLrLbGsl6T6DjljGpqGFdKiYENjI2eaeGplDoA5Z7qWQovGZOjBy8vkq4LH7bdbw3mx_sCUl0uzZfalfr4cYcV02fQSUw9rnuO7Zwwg08YvpDal_UH27Rgxtp_ECZob8JKS2NHIQz9QukUhVFMW8tIVw6lb-V_0T8CYZOT" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
           Machine Learning and Security: Protecting Systems with Data and Algorithms
          </a>
         </em>
         .
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Fun fact: Clarence is also in the GeekPwn Hall of Fame for successfully misleading a machine learning system.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         One more fun fact: in 2019, Clarence became a lecturer at Berkeley in Applied Machine Learning.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         OK, back to that personal experience. Shape protected large customers' websites from hackers. Part of Clarence\xe2\x80\x99s job was to take descriptions of attack patterns from security operations professionals, and write rules to defend against them. One night on rotation, he took in a description, wrote a rule, deployed, and closed his computer. He got a frantic call four hours later letting him know that the client\xe2\x80\x99s site had been down the entire four hours since he deployed,
         <strong>
          costing them $2 million per hour
         </strong>
         in bookings! Clarence wasn\xe2\x80\x99t fired for the error, but it did light a fire in him.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         He realized that the disconnect between what ops people know and what they can do is a cause of a lot of problems:
        </p>
        <ol style="margin: 1em 0;">
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Things are lost in translation between ops and engineering.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           There is a time lag between when the ops people see something and when engineers can implement a fix during which attackers can get in and wreak havoc.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Ops and engineering teams resent each other.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Even if everything worked perfectly, there just aren\xe2\x80\x99t enough engineers to solve all of the challenges companies face.
          </p>
         </li>
        </ol>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Clarence left Shape in 2017. Trisha left Affirm in 2018. Both were thinking about the same problem from different angles. And both joined
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkM2urCAQhJ9mWBp-BRcszua8BuGnR8koGMBrfPuL4-Ikne5FpbpSn7cN5lwuvefa0L1Mu3bQCc66QmtQ0FGhmBg0Galigk8oaB6IEgrFat4FYLNx1a0cgPbDrdHbFnP6OjCmAi16nFgArmyQxBMyUeylpZYHzN9gp_H95NojREgeNPyDcuUEaNVLa3t9sZ8X_e1znudQ89GW3ZaPz9uWUx367RKKmmJKsMSKUCEEG8hAyOiIZA5zLoPF1GHpOXOcED466_iL422mQz1cbdZ_7k-o6JSbyyWmucufxW6wfoVezdyRR4rtMpCsWyE8rdsD78vBzJCgdKjB2HYjE5KraWRM4adlx8KUIHKaCOrJIXdX-gv9D0T_hd8" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          South Park Commons
         </a>
         (SPC), a vibrant \xe2\x80\x9ccommunity of builders, tinkerers, and domain experts\xe2\x80\x9d in San Francisco. SPC isn\xe2\x80\x99t an incubator; it\xe2\x80\x99s a place to explore new ideas before they\xe2\x80\x99re anything at all. Trisha and Clarence met at SPC, and decided to explore together, specifically in the Anti-Money Laundering (AML) space.
        </p>
        <div class="captioned-image-container-static" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 16px; text-align: center;">
         <figure style="display: inline-block; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;">
          <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="image-wrapper" style="margin: 8px auto; mso-padding-alt: 1em 0 1.6em;" width="100%">
           <tbody>
            <tr>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
             </td>
             <td align="left" class="content" style="text-align: center;" width="550">
              <a class="image-link" href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxVUsuOpDAM_JrmBsqThAOH0Ur7G8hJDB01JGwSZrbn6yfAYbVSZDu27LKqbKHgEtN73GMuzWmm8t5xDPiVVywFU3NkTJN3I-2Z5lIMjRuFo1rqxudpTogb-HUs6cBmP8zqLRQfw9VBCJPNczTKCiCEzyjEICwVvVHKaTP0Qkir-xsXDucxWBzxE9M7BmzW8VnKnh_848F-12dd6PJhcgH76mzcaspvsGD1Mxb7PH0dU-KD_fpzB_xjidHV_7xOe4pLwpz9J9Z8Loh77bghmDxB5AlTjTnsC2s9tUikMVaL1gDwVnCF7SCpbsEZzgwqNWjRZd7BBt8xwFe-96ozbi6u8FoyX6ECjc4w1lJl6zzkvAVwpKUOlWBq5prAVIf-5T3v9rA0fmSEUaKIpkxKyTvaUdobqrghQigHhBlS-eVG0JNYMOIhyLaw_5hq0hhiMTH5sNTy6wkbrlehrjlVvx3Bl_eEAcyK7laz3Edx6TstGDDVY3ETlPMUpBJ66Hnd91avys21pGoYaFORXaxd4R_oD1zPxuQ" style="border: none; display: block; height: auto; margin: 0; padding: 0; text-decoration: none; width: auto;" target="_blank">
               <img alt="" class="wide-image" data-attrs='{"src":"https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7a8edb22-17c3-4e33-aad0-1de7427f380a_798x363.png","height":363,"width":798,"resizeWidth":null,"bytes":null,"alt":null,"title":null,"type":null,"href":null}' src="https://cdn.substack.com/image/fetch/w_1596,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7a8edb22-17c3-4e33-aad0-1de7427f380a_798x363.png" style="-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; border: none !important; display: block; height: auto; margin: 0 auto; margin-bottom: 0; max-width: 550px; vertical-align: middle; width: 100%;" width="550"/>
              </a>
             </td>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
             </td>
            </tr>
           </tbody>
          </table>
         </figure>
        </div>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         The duo did what so many aspiring founders do: reached out to potential customers to find out if there was a \xe2\x80\x9cthere\xe2\x80\x9d there. Specifically, they reached out to 300 people with \xe2\x80\x9cAnti-Money Laundering\xe2\x80\x9d in their title on LinkedIn to learn about their challenges and appetite for a solution.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         One of those people was the head of AML at eBay. He told them he was doing an RFP in three weeks, and that they should submit their company. It\xe2\x80\x99s just... they didn\xe2\x80\x99t have a company yet.
        </p>
        <h3 style="-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: 'SF Compact Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;">
         <strong>
          Meet Unit21
         </strong>
        </h3>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Over those next three weeks, Trisha and Clarence did a lot:
        </p>
        <ul style="margin: 1em 0;">
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Figured out what an \xe2\x80\x9cRFP\xe2\x80\x9d is
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Incorporated Unit21, Inc.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Built a prototype
          </p>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Then, they showed up to eBay\xe2\x80\x99s HQ in San Jose. They brought along one of Kothari\xe2\x80\x99s former Affirm colleagues to make the team look a little bigger.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         The three of them presented the prototype that they\xe2\x80\x99d built over the last 20 days, went home, and then heard from eBay\xe2\x80\xa6 that they were the front-runner out of four chosen finalists. Of the other three, the smallest was a $3 billion company. Unit21 was three weeks old and worth $0 on paper.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         How was three-week-old Unit21 even a contender?
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         In the past, there were two ways that companies built their AML/fraud models:
        </p>
        <ol style="margin: 1em 0;">
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Built something fully custom in-house using internal engineering teams.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Bought something off the shelf from a vendor and spent half a million or so dollars to customize it.
          </p>
         </li>
        </ol>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         In the latter case, companies would buy a product, integrate it into their system, tweak the inputs, and then trust a black box to spit out when a transaction was suspicious. They often erred on the side of being too cautious, sending humans a rash of false positives to sift through.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Every AML product with which Unit21 competes offers transaction monitoring that looks at a few things like who the payment is to and from, what industry they\xe2\x80\x99re in, what country the payment is going to, and the volume and value of transactions. They look at the data and assign a risk score, and higher-risk transactions are sent to humans for review.
        </p>
        <div class="captioned-image-container-static" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 16px; text-align: center;">
         <figure style="display: inline-block; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;">
          <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="image-wrapper" style="margin: 8px auto; mso-padding-alt: 1em 0 1.6em;" width="100%">
           <tbody>
            <tr>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
             </td>
             <td align="left" class="content" style="text-align: center;" width="550">
